reviews.review_text: God's Little Party Favors ! Thanks To Charlie, Scott And Hess For All They Do. Great Show, Grate Memories To Brighten Your Day !

nit picking every note the second set starts with Sugar Mags, not "space" or So What. jeez , they are fucking around , you don't have to catalog EVERY note played.
Nice Ballad of a Thin Man.

Nice FM source and transfer  Hey GD fans,    yep , this is a great performance by the GD.  I think it's part of the "download series " on iTunes but it's not really the same mix ... I think?  I haven't really done a comparison but FM, or "frequency modulation" maybe that's reason I LIKE this mix.  Back before all the flac and downloads we had this think called "analog" format, well; let's most of us were simply happy with a sound board or FM broadcast. For me, this was a relatively "fresh" recording of the GD, so it was cool in that right alone! A big kudos to the taper "hess" with the Sony D5 deck and some kind of FM receiver  or maybe he was line out from a boom box?  I think my original 3rd gen tape was from a boom box that had not the best reception and more importantly a improper bias for chrome tapes, so the high end was not that correct "EQ".  This is a great source with correct EQ and good FM source without static as in some others out there .. 

However,  a strong 1st and 2nd set with a somewhat "regular" set list with the exception of "to lay me down" and "ballad of a thin man" which had been always rare in my opinion, and a split "sugar magnolia" and the reprise of "sunshine daydream" motif !  However, the verve and sweat of this performance was a testament that the GD were strong ; something that many nay sayers would say even back then?

A little background on the "in house FM" Dan Healy, the GD's front of house sound pro decided that he would employ a low wattage FM brodacast for the "parking lot" and thus , you have a FM board recording.  However, I read later in Relix magazine the FCC had registered a complaint of such broadcasts and the bottom line is: can't do it with out a bunch of red tape crap, or i.e. has to be from a legitimate licensed local radio station, of which the GD has done for eon's . I tip my hat to the GD for their innovation.   It's crazy , it can be done with Wi-Fi for sure ... 

anyway,  this is a keeper show and probably the best show of 1988 ...   a kiiller Scarlet > Fire , you can hear the audience gasp at times !
